FLOW A: GENERATE SCHEDULE (VENUS-LIKE)

Screen: “Generate Schedule”

Layout:
- Left side: “Schedule Criteria” panel.
- Right side: “Generated Schedules” area with a tabbed view (e.g., “Grid view” and “List view”) and a weekly calendar preview.

Criteria panel fields:
- Term selector (dropdown, default to starting semester).
- Required Courses: pill inputs where user types course codes (e.g., “CMSC330”) and they autocomplete to full course names. Each required course displays as a chip with a small remove icon.
- Optional Courses: same pattern, but visually distinguished (lighter border).
- Credits:
  - Min Credits (dropdown: 12–18)
  - Max Credits (dropdown: 12–21)
- Waitlist / Section filters:
  - Toggle: “Only show open sections”
  - Optional dropdown for “Waitlist seats minimum”
- Delivery & Location:
  - Delivery method multiselect: Face-to-Face, Blended, Online
  - Location/Program dropdown: College Park, Shady Grove, etc.
- Time & Day Exclusions:
  - A simple control to block times: e.g., horizontal timeline for each weekday with “Add blocked time” button or checkboxes for “No classes before X” and “No classes after Y”.
  - Example: “No classes before 10:00 AM” or “Block M/W 5–7 PM”.
- Clear/Reset button at bottom of criteria card.

Main actions:
- Primary button: “Generate Schedules”
- After schedules are generated:
  - Show a row of schedule thumbnails (e.g., Schedule A, B, C) with a small summary (number of days on campus, earliest class, latest class, total credits).
  - Clicking one opens a larger weekly calendar with colored blocks.
  - Each section card shows course code, title, section number, instructor (placeholder), and core attributes.
  - Buttons: “Save this schedule”, “Export to calendar” (future), “Send to Four-Year Plan”.

---

FLOW B: EXPLORE SCHEDULES / BUILD MY WEEK (COURSE PLANNER-LIKE)

Screen: “Build My Week”

Layout:
- Left side: Search and filters.
- Right side: Weekly calendar.

Left panel:
- Title: “Find Courses”
- Search bar: supports searching by course code, title, or Gen Ed code (e.g., DSHU, DVUP).
- Filters:
  - Semester
  - Departments (dropdown / multiselect)
  - Gen Ed tags (FSAR, DSHU, DVUP, etc.)
  - Level (100 / 200 / 300 / 400)
  - Credits range
  - Days (M/T/W/Th/F)
- Results list:
  - Each result in a card: course code, title, credits, Gen Ed tags, brief description, and a “View sections” button.
  - “Add to calendar” button per section.

Right panel:
- Weekly calendar view (Mon–Fri, plus optional Sat).
- When a course is added, show colored time blocks with labels (code, short title, building/room placeholder).
- Hover shows details; click to open a side panel with full description, seat info placeholder, and buttons:
  - “Move to a different section”
  - “Remove from week”
  - “Add to Four-Year Plan”
- Above calendar: small summary bar showing total credits, earliest start time, latest end time.

