FLOW C: FOUR-YEAR PLAN SETUP AND VIEW

C1 – “Import Your Credits”

Title:
- “Let’s start with what you’ve already earned”

Subtitle:
- “Tell us about AP, transfer, exemption, and other credits so we don’t double-count anything.”

Layout:
- Form with repeating rows for previously earned credits.
- Fields per row:
  - Source type (dropdown): AP, IB, Transfer from another university, Exemption exam, For-credit exam, Other.
  - Original course/exam name (e.g., “AP Calculus BC”).
  - UMD equivalent course code (text input with autocomplete, e.g., MATH140).
  - Credits (numeric).
  - Term awarded (optional).
- Button: “Add another credit”
- Info banner: “You can edit these later from your Profile > Credits.”
- Primary button: “Next: Gen Eds”

C2 – “Gen Eds Overview” (Jupiterp-style but cleaner)

Model the content after a cleaned-up version of the Gen Eds sheet and Jupiterp’s Gen Eds table.

Layout:
- Title: “General Education Progress”
- Summary row: show four small cards:
  - Fundamental Studies: X / Y courses
  - Distributive Studies: X / Y courses
  - I-Series / Big Question: X / Y courses
  - Diversity: X / Y courses
- Below: a table of Gen Ed codes.

Table columns:
- Gen Ed code (e.g., FSAW, FSMA, DSHU, DSHS, DSNL, DSNS, DSSP, SCIS, DVUP, DVCC)
- Category (Fundamental Studies / Distributive Studies / I-Series / Diversity)
- Status (Not started / In progress / Completed)
- Required count
- Completed count
- Remaining count
- Fulfilled by (course list with term, like “MUSC204 (Spring 2026)”)
- “View options” link/button.

Color coding:
- Completed rows: subtle green highlight and green status pill.
- In-progress rows: subtle blue highlight and blue status pill.
- Not started: neutral.

Interaction:
- Clicking a Gen Ed row or “View options” opens a side panel or modal:
  - Shows explanation of that requirement (e.g., “Analytic Reasoning requirement.”)
  - Shows a searchable list of courses that satisfy it (integrate with course search pattern from Build My Week).
  - Button: “Add planned course to Four-Year Plan.”

C3 – “[Major] Degree Requirements – Structure Builder”

This is the complex screen where the user models the catalog.

Title:
- “[Major] Degree Requirements”
Subtitle:
- “Copy the structure from the UMD catalog and turn it into interactive sections OrbitUMD can track.”

Layout:
- Left: instructions + link box.
  - Text: “Open your major in the UMD catalog, then recreate its sections here.”
  - Button/link: “Open my major in UMD Catalog” (placeholder/link box).
  - Short bullet-like hints: 
    - “Use sections like ‘Required Lower Level Courses’ or ‘Upper Level Electives’.”
    - “Mark whether all courses are required or if students must choose X from a list.”
- Right: the interactive requirements builder.

Requirements builder:
- Sections appear stacked vertically as cards.

Each Section card contains:
- Section title input (e.g., “Required Lower Level Courses”).
- Section type:
  - Radio buttons / dropdown:
    - “All courses in this section are required”
    - “Choose X courses from this section”
- If “Choose X” selected: numeric input for X.
- Course list area:
  - Rows, each with:
    - Course code input (with autocomplete, e.g., CMSC330).
    - Course title (auto-filled or small secondary text).
    - A grouping control area:
      - Buttons: “Group with &” and “Group with OR” that allow the user to define groups like `(Course A AND Course B) OR (Course C AND Course D)`.
  - Visual grouping:
    - Use brackets or pill groups to show grouped courses clearly, with labels like “(Group 1: AND)” or “(Group 2: OR)”.
- At bottom of each section card:
  - Button: “Add course”
  - Button: “Add group (AND / OR group)”
  - Small text: “Example: (PHYS161 AND PHYS261) OR (PHYS171 AND PHYS174).”

Below all sections:
- Button: “Add new section” (lightweight, appears as a faint card prompt beneath existing sections).
- Primary button: “Save [Major] Requirements”
- If user has additional majors/minors:
  - After saving, show a modal: “Add requirements for [Second Major/Minor]?” with “Yes, set up now” or “Skip for later.”

---

C4 – DEGREE AUDIT SUMMARY

Once requirements and credits are in, show a Degree Audit screen.

Title:
- “Degree Audit”
Subtitle:
- “A clean summary of what you’ve done, what’s in progress, and what’s left to graduate.”

Layout:
- Left: filter sidebar.
  - Filters:
    - View: “All”, “Gen Eds”, “Majors”, “Minors”, “Upper Level Concentration”
    - Status: “Completed”, “In progress”, “Planned”, “Unfulfilled”
- Right: main audit content in grouped cards.

For each requirement group (e.g., “Total Credits”, “General Education”, “Computer Science Major”, “Physics Major”, “Upper Level Concentration”):
- Card header:
  - Group name
  - Progress bar (e.g., 68/120 credits, 14/40 Gen Ed credits).
  - Status: OK / In progress / Unfulfilled.
- Inside card:
  - Subrequirements listed similarly to UMD’s audit but cleaner:
    - Line item: requirement name + small status pill + requirement details.
    - Example: “Upper Level CS Courses · In Progress · Need 5 courses from 3 areas.”
    - Under each, show the specific courses that are:
      - Completed (green chip, with course code, title, term).
      - In progress (blue chip).
      - Planned (grey chip).
  - Every course chip is clickable:
    - Click → context menu:
      - “View course details”
      - “Jump to schedule containing this course”
      - “Jump to Four-Year Plan cell”

Also include:
- A global summary card at top with:
  - Total credits completed / in progress / remaining.
  - Cumulative GPA placeholder.
  - Quick links: “Open Four-Year Plan”, “Generate Schedule for next term”.

---

C5 – FOUR-YEAR PLAN GRID (CORE VIEW)

Screen: “Four-Year Plan”

Layout:
- Tabs across top:
  - “Plan by Semester”
  - “Requirements”
  - “Gen Eds”
  - “Credits & Transfers”
- By default, show “Plan by Semester”.

Plan by Semester:
- A grid with rows = terms (e.g., “Fall 2025, Spring 2026, …”), columns = planned courses in that term.
- Each term row:
  - Left label: Term name + credits total for that term.
  - A row of course chips/cards:
    - Each card shows: course code, short title, credits, requirement tags (e.g., DSHU, Major, Minor).
    - Color ring or small label indicates status: completed, in progress, planned.
- At bottom:
  - “Add term” button (for extra summers or winters).
- Clicking a course card:
  - Open side panel with:
    - Full course description.
    - Which requirement(s) it fulfills.
    - Buttons: “Move to another term” (with dropdown), “Send to Build My Week”, “Remove from plan”.

Requirements tab:
- Show a high-level tree: Gen Eds, each Major, each Minor.
- Each node shows a progress bar and a count of requirements remaining.
- Click any node to jump to its section in the Degree Audit screen.

Gen Eds tab:
- Reuse the Gen Eds table UI from earlier but integrated with plan data.

Credits & Transfers tab:
- List all imported credits (AP, transfer, etc.) with the mapped UMD course and where they’re being applied (e.g., “Counts toward FSAR and MATH requirement”).

